µC1Method: Portable demosµC4

There are a lot of good multiplatform libraries to use in demos, which make the same code compilable on all platforms. You might use SDL for display and timing, SDL_image for pictures, OpenGL for 3d graphics and fmod for music. You can't use assembly code, but libraries are optimized and 3d cards make this issue uninteresting. The major drawback is the shared libraries the user must have installed.

